info.name: Marketstack
info.description: **Easy-to-use REST API interface delivering worldwide stock market data in JSON format.** ## **Quickstart Guide** ### Step 1: Fork the collection To get started quickly, you need to fork the Marketstack Postman Collection. Simply click the button below to fork it. [](https://god.gw.postman.com/run-collection/10131015-9cbac391-3611-4f50-9bfd-d24ae41c97c1?action=collection/fork) ### Step 2: Get your API Access Key 1. Go to the [Marketstack](https://marketstack.com/?utm_source=Postman&utm_medium=Referral) website and choose the right subscription plan for your particular project. 2. Get your personal API Access Key on the [Dashboard](https://marketstack.com/dashboard) to authenticate with the API. Keep it safe! You can reset it at any time in your Account Dashboard. ## Step 3: Make your first API call Marketstack Postman collection contains all the endpoints supported by Marketstack API. 1. End-of-Day Data 2. Intraday Data 3. Real-Time Updates 4. Historical Data 5. Splits Data 6. Dividends Data 7. Tickers 8. Exchanges 9. Currencies 10. Timezones We recommend you to start with the End-of-Day Data endpoint as it's primary endpoint. It is used to obtain end-of-day data for one or multiple stock tickers. A single or multiple comma-separated ticker symbols are passed to the API using the symbols parameter.
